Security Policy

Last updated: April 2026

1. Security Approach

BrewStation is designed to operate entirely on the user’s device without requiring internet connectivity or external communication.

2. Local Data Handling

All application data, settings, and saved states remain stored locally on the user’s device. No data is transmitted to external servers or third parties.

3. Permissions

BrewStation requests only the system permissions necessary to perform its core functionality, including disk access required for saving and restoring application-related data.

4. Data Protection

BrewStation does not use remote databases, cloud storage, analytics platforms, or third-party services that process user data.

5. Vulnerability Reporting

If you discover a security issue or vulnerability related to BrewStation, please report it by email so it can be reviewed and addressed promptly.

6. Contact

For security-related questions or reports, please contact: hreinssondev@gmail.com
